item.title: Grand Circle Island and Haleiwa 9 Hour Tour
item.description: Perfect for first-time visitors, or those with limited time, this full-day tour takes you all around Oahu, making sure that you don't miss a thing. You'll explore top attractions including Diamond Head, Hanauma Bay, Halona Blowhole, the Byodo-In Temple and the surfing beaches of the North Shore. You'll also have enough time to discover the charming town of Haleiwa.

image.alt: Grand Circle Island and Haleiwa 9 Hour Tour

item.title: Chicago Architecture River Cruise
item.description: Admire some of the Windy City's most iconic views—and enjoy a time-saving, relaxing way to sightsee—aboard this Chicago River architecture boat tour. With commentary from your onboard guide, watch the spectacular skyline glide by, including dozens of notable buildings, like the Wrigley Building and the John Hancock Building. In just one tour, you'll cover multiple branches of the Chicago River, and will learn insider facts and stories you'd otherwise miss.

image.alt: Chicago Architecture River Cruise

item.title: History and Hauntings of Salem Guided Walking Tour
item.description: Learn about Salem’s mysterious past on this guided walking tour of the city. Follow your historian guide through Salem, listening to 400 years of history, and admire the old architecture that dates back to the early colonial period. Find out the truth about the 1692 Salem Witch Trial hysteria, which has influenced literature and pop culture. For a spookier experience, select the nighttime tour led by lantern light.

image.alt: History and Hauntings of Salem Guided Walking Tour

item.title: New York in One Day Guided Sightseeing Tour
item.description: Make the most of your time in the city that never sleeps on a guided tour of NYC’s top attractions. Travel by both the Staten Island Ferry and bus as you swing by the 9/11 Memorial, Central Park, Rockefeller Center and more. Then hop aboard a one-trip Ferry ride for a sightseeing cruise past the Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island, complete with stunning views of the world-famous skyline and Brooklyn Bridge.

image.alt: New York in One Day Guided Sightseeing Tour

item.title: New Orleans Premier Ghost, Voodoo & Vampire Walking Tour
item.description: Exploring New Orleans in the evening can seem like an intimidating quest on your own, but this ghost, voodoo, and vampire walking tour takes you to the city’s most eerie sites at night in the safety of a group with a knowledgeable guide. Stop by top attractions such as the LaLaurie Mansion and New Orleans Pharmacy Museum, all while listening to your guide’s detailed stories of the paranormal and beyond.

image.alt: New Orleans Premier Ghost, Voodoo & Vampire Walking Tour

item.title: Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island Tour: All Options
item.description: One of the US’ most iconic symbols, the Statue of Liberty rises up from New York Harbor, welcoming the immigrants who once entered through nearby Ellis Island. Visit Lady Liberty and learn the stories of those who passed through Ellis Island on this convenient tour with options that let you choose how long you want to spend at each attraction. Opt to visit the Ellis Island National Museum of Immigration.

image.alt: Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island Tour: All Options

item.title: Grand Canyon West Tour with Hoover Dam Stop and Optional Skywalk
item.description: This Grand Canyon day tour offers an all-inclusive experience with exclusive perks. Avoid the crowds as you travel in a luxury bus, picking up from select hotels in Las Vegas. On the way to the West Rim, enjoy a hot, sit-down breakfast at a restaurant and stop at the Hoover Dam Memorial Bridge for stunning photo opportunities. At the Grand Canyon, you'll have VIP bus access, allowing you to spend more time exploring without the need to transfer to shuttle buses. The tour includes admission to the West Rim, a scenic BBQ lunch on the canyon rim and two bottles of ice-cold water, returning to Las Vegas around 5pm.

image.alt: Grand Canyon West Tour with Hoover Dam Stop and Optional Skywalk

item.title: Grand Canyon West, Hoover Dam Stop and Optional Lunch and Skywalk
item.description: Enjoy a seamless journey from Las Vegas to the stunning Grand Canyon West, one of the most iconic destinations in the world. Relax in an air-conditioned vehicle and spend your day marveling at the awe-inspiring views from Eagle Point and Guano Point, and immerse yourself in the rich culture of the Hualapai Tribe. For an even more unforgettable experience, customize your tour by adding a Grand Canyon Skywalk ticket, giving you a thrilling perspective over the canyon’s edge.

image.alt: Grand Canyon West, Hoover Dam Stop and Optional Lunch and Skywalk

item.title: Charleston’s Old South Carriage Historic Horse & Carriage Tour
item.description: Experience more than 300 years of history on this guided carriage tour of Charleston. See the many mansions, churches, and gardens as your horse-drawn carriage tour covers more than 2.5 miles and 30 blocks of historic Charleston. Belgian and Percheron draft horses will you lead you through the streets while you learn about this “Holy City” and its role in the Civil War.

image.alt: Charleston’s Old South Carriage Historic Horse & Carriage Tour

item.title: Exclusive Niagara Falls US Tour W/Boat Ride, Cave & More Wonders!
item.description: Experience one of nature's most popular attractions from three vantage points on this half-day tour of Niagara Falls (American side). Visit the Cave of the Winds, and take a cruise to the base of Horseshoe Falls on the famous Maid of the Mist (early May to late October). Descend to the bottom of Niagara Gorge in an elevator, before heading upwards to soak in the scene from Prospect Point Observation Tower. There's plenty of time for photo ops to capture the famous falls on camera.

image.alt: Exclusive Niagara Falls US Tour W/Boat Ride, Cave & More Wonders!

item.title: Chicago River 90-Minute Architecture Tour
item.description: Discover the architectural gems of the Windy City from an ideal vantage point on a cruise down the Chicago River. Offered several times throughout the day, it’s easy to fit the leisurely excursion into your itinerary. Covering more than 130 years of architectural history, the tour is the perfect opportunity to see a huge area of the city without the hassle of taxis and public transit.

image.alt: Chicago River 90-Minute Architecture Tour

item.title: Chicago: Gangsters and Ghosts Walking Tour
item.description: Experience a colorful side of Chicago history with this gangsters and ghosts tour. With a historian as your guide, you’ll step back to the Roaring Twenties, when the Chicago Loop was a hub for bootleggers, speakeasies, and gangsters like the infamous Al Capone. Visit onetime gangster hangouts and haunted sites like the Palmer House, Congress Hotel, and Death Alley. Upgrade to experience the tour by minibus.

image.alt: Chicago: Gangsters and Ghosts Walking Tour

item.title: Little Havana Food and Walking Tour in Miami
item.description: Experience the sights and sounds of Miami’s vibrant Little Havana neighborhood on this guided walking food tour. Explore this lively Cuban district and learn about its fascinating history and culture, with stops at some of the best family-owned and operated Cuban restaurants in the area. Sample the local cuisine, like guava pastries, chicken plantain cups, and flan ice cream, to name just a few of the delicacies offered along the way. Also, meet some of the local artists, watch skilled Cuban cigar rollers and listen to traditional Cuban music.

image.alt: Little Havana Food and Walking Tour in Miami

item.title: Half-Day Mojave Desert ATV Tour from Las Vegas
item.description: Experience the thrills of riding an all-terrain vehicle (ATV) through the Mojave Desert on this half-day guided ATV tour from Las Vegas. After meeting on the Strip, you will be transported to just outside the Lake Mead Recreation Area. After an orientation, ride for 1.5 hours on a private track exclusive to this tour.

image.alt: Half-Day Mojave Desert ATV Tour from Las Vegas

item.title: Niagara Falls in 1 Day: Tour of American and Canadian Sides
item.description: Some Niagara Falls tours are American and some are Canadian. Not this one. Get the full experience from both sides of the border on this deluxe tour of everything Niagara Falls has to offer. Visit all the must-see Niagara Falls attractions, from the thrilling Maid of the Mist boat cruise to the exciting Cave of the Winds walk—even a trip to the top of the Skylon Tower and much more. All attraction and admission fees, plus hotel transfers and road tolls are included. Food and beverages are at your own expense.

image.alt: Niagara Falls in 1 Day: Tour of American and Canadian Sides

item.title: Beneath The Streets Underground History Tour
item.description: Discover Seattle’s original neighborhood, Pioneer Square, on this guided walking tour. Explore the underground pathways that were built in the southwest corner of the Emerald City more than 120 years ago. Learn about Seattle’s history and the events that transformed this once-small Indigenous dwelling place into one of the most popular and thriving cities in the United States. Each small-group tour is unique, with insider tips from a professional, local guide.

image.alt: Beneath The Streets Underground History Tour

item.title: Honolulu Xtreme Parasail
item.description: Fly 500 feet (152 meters) above the scenic coast of Oahu on this 1-hour parasailing adventure from Waikiki. Buckle in to a harness and take off from the boat, soaring over the south shore of the islands for spectacular views. Photo packages available for purchase on the boat. No experience is necessary; this activity is suitable for participants of all experience levels. Parasail 500 feet (152 meters) above the Oahu coast Get fantastic views of the island's southern shore No experience necessary.

image.alt: Honolulu Xtreme Parasail

item.title: Ultimate Hoover Dam Tour from Las Vegas with Lunch
item.description: Experience a VIP tour of the Hoover Dam with early access to avoid the crowds. Enjoy a guided "Walk on the Top" tour, a powerplant tour inside the dam, stunning views from the memorial bridge, and admission to the Visitor Center exhibits. The tour includes a freshly cooked lunch at a restaurant and a bonus ticket to the LA Comedy Club at The Strat, a $45 value. Hotel pickup and drop-off, bottled water, and air-conditioned transport are all part of this exclusive experience.

image.alt: Ultimate Hoover Dam Tour from Las Vegas with Lunch

item.title: The Haygoods: Branson's Most Popular Show
item.description: Buy your tickets in advance for the Haygoods show in Branson, Missouri, to plan your vacation ahead of time. Guarantee your admission to this popular show to avoid sold-out days or times. Listen to a talented family providing music and dance with special effects and more than 20 different instruments.

image.alt: The Haygoods: Branson's Most Popular Show

item.title: DC Monuments and Memorials Night Tour
item.description: Ride a luxury mini-coach past major landmarks on this night bus tour of Washington DC. Gaze at floodlit memorials and monuments, such as the magnificent Lincoln Memorial and the glow of the Jefferson Memorial reflected in the Tidal Basin. After this sightseeing tour, you’ll understand why the nation’s capital is considered one of the world’s most beautiful cities at night.

image.alt: DC Monuments and Memorials Night Tour

item.title: 9/11 Memorial Museum Admission Ticket
item.description: Prebook your admission to the 9/11 Memorial Museum in lower Manhattan, and guarantee your entry to the center that documented the terrorist attacks on the World Trade Center in 2001. Museum artifacts include first-person accounts of what happened on that September morning in 2001, multi-media displays, and exhibits on history, which commemorate nearly 3,000 people who lost their lives in the attacks.

image.alt: 9/11 Memorial Museum Admission Ticket

item.title: Juneau Wildlife Whale Watching
item.description: When your cruise stops at Juneau, see whales in their natural habitat on this whale-watching boat trip, all without the fuss of organizing shore transport. Prebook to secure your place, board a comfortable boat with outdoor decks and heated cabins, and cruise Alaska’s waters to see marine life in the wild. Then, enjoy guaranteed sightings of humpback whales, with a naturalist providing commentary on their behaviors as you cruise.

image.alt: Juneau Wildlife Whale Watching

item.title: Big Island in a Day: Volcanoes Waterfalls Sightseeing and History
item.description: The Big Island of Hawaii has a diverse ecosystem unlike anywhere else on the planet, and on this day-long nature tour, experience the beauty of its black-sand beaches, thundering waterfalls, and Hawaii Volcanoes National Park. If you’re lucky, find Hawaiian green sea turtles basking on the coast. Since the tour only requires a moderate amount of walking, it's an educational adventure for travelers of all ages, with snacks and refreshments included.

image.alt: Big Island in a Day: Volcanoes Waterfalls Sightseeing and History

item.title: Private Central Park Pedicab Tour
item.description: One of New York City’s most celebrated sights, Central Park is a vast green space plum in the heart of Manhattan. With this private pedicab tour, see more of this leafy oasis than possible on foot in the same time, and hear stories of highlights such as Bethesda Fountain and the Strawberry Fields John Lennon memorial from a guide—insight you might miss if you were going it alone.

image.alt: Private Central Park Pedicab Tour
